                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.30/182: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-04T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 4, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>971. My 967 July 3, 6 p.m. I happened to meet Rochat late yesterday evening. He
                    informed me that according to a telegram received <pb facs="0222" n="216"
                        xml:id="pg_216"/> yesterday afternoon from Admiral Godefroy at Alexandria,
                    the British had made no demands of any kind in connection with the French
                    squadron there. Rochat wished me to know this chiefly because of unsubstantiated
                    reports which were afloat in Vichy yesterday to the effect that the British
                    intended to scuttle the French Fleet in Alexandria.</p>
                <p>Rochat added that after our conversation with Laval yesterday afternoon Admiral
                    Auphan had expressed to him his conviction that if the French Government were to
                    comply with the suggestion and offer of the United States Government he was
                    certain that the German Government would demand the cession of an equal amount
                    of tonnage of French war vessels now lying in French ports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tuck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
